    highlights: [
      "Solve quadratic equations with step-by-step breakdowns that show both the formula and the intermediate calculations.",
      "Simplify, add, subtract, multiply, and divide fractions with an interactive calculator designed for students and teachers.",
      "Compute percentages, ratios, and proportions instantly for shopping discounts, grade calculations, and everyday math.",
      "Graph linear and quadratic functions to visualize equations and better understand slope, intercepts, and vertex points.",
      "Calculate mean, median, mode, range, and standard deviation for any data set with one paste of your numbers.",
      "Convert between number systems including binary, octal, decimal, and hexadecimal for programming and digital logic work.",
    ],
  },
  pdf: {
    intro: "The PDF tools collection on ToolNestr transforms how you work with portable document files by giving you powerful editing and conversion capabilities directly in your browser. You can merge multiple PDFs into a single document, split large files into smaller chapters or pages, compress bloated files for easier emailing, and convert between PDF and other formats like Word, Excel, or images without uploading sensitive documents to unknown servers. Everything happens securely on your device, preserving your privacy while delivering professional-quality results. Whether you are a student assembling a research portfolio, an office worker preparing monthly reports, or a freelancer sending polished proposals, these tools eliminate the need for expensive desktop software. ToolNestr handles files of reasonable size quickly and maintains formatting fidelity throughout each operation.",
    highlights: [
      "Merge multiple PDF files into one organized document with customizable page ordering and no quality loss.",
      "Split large PDFs into individual pages or custom page ranges for easier sharing and archiving.",
      "Compress PDF file size significantly while preserving readability to meet email attachment limits and save storage space.",
      "Convert PDFs to editable Word documents, Excel spreadsheets, or high-quality images without losing formatting.",
      "Rotate, reorder, and delete individual pages from your PDF using a simple drag-and-drop interface.",
      "Protect your PDFs with password encryption or add watermarks to assert ownership and prevent unauthorized sharing.",
    ],
  },
  creators: {
    intro: "ToolNestr's Creator Toolkit is built for content creators, social media managers, designers, and anyone who produces digital content regularly. This category brings together utilities that streamline the repetitive parts of content creation so you can focus on the creative work that really matters. Generate color palettes from uploaded images, create mock text for design layouts, count social media characters with platform-specific limits, and check contrast ratios for accessibility compliance. Each tool is purpose-built for the kind of fast, iterative workflow that creators depend on, with results that update in real time as you tweak your inputs. ToolNestr keeps these tools available wherever you are, whether you are drafting a caption on your phone or preparing visuals on a desktop, without requiring any installations or subscriptions.",
    highlights: [
      "Extract color palettes from any uploaded image to build consistent brand schemes and design systems in seconds.",
      "Check social media character counts against platform-specific limits for Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn, and Facebook posts.",
      "Generate realistic placeholder text and images for wireframes, mockups, and design prototypes during early development.",
      "Test color contrast ratios against WCAG accessibility standards to ensure your content is readable by all audiences.",
      "Create CSS gradient code visually by clicking and dragging color stops, then copy the output directly into your stylesheet.",
      "Resize and crop images for specific social media dimensions with preset templates that match each platform's requirements.",
    ],
  },
  developers: {
    intro: "The Developer Tools section on ToolNestr is a productivity hub for programmers, web developers, and IT professionals who need reliable utilities at their fingertips. From formatting messy JSON and minifying CSS to decoding Base64 strings and generating UUIDs, these tools handle the tedious but essential tasks that interrupt deep work. Each utility runs entirely in the browser, so there is no data leakage and no waiting for server round trips, just instant results as you type or paste. The collection also includes hashing tools, HTML entity encoders, syntax highlighters, and regular expression testers that help you debug and validate code quickly. ToolNestr designed this category with the developer workflow in mind, making sure every tool produces output that is easy to copy, share, or integrate into your projects without extra formatting steps.",
    highlights: [
      "Format, validate, and minify JSON data with configurable indentation to spot syntax errors and reduce file size instantly.",
      "Generate UUIDs and GUIDs in multiple versions for database keys, session identifiers, and distributed system references.",
      "Encode and decode Base64 strings, URL parameters, and HTML entities for secure data transmission and display.",
      "Test regular expressions against sample text with real-time match highlighting and detailed group capture breakdowns.",
      "Hash strings using MD5, SHA-1, SHA-256, and SHA-512 algorithms for data integrity checks and password verification.",
      "Minify CSS and JavaScript source code to reduce page load times and optimize website performance for end users.",
    ],
  },
  engineering: {
    intro: "ToolNestr's Engineering category provides a focused set of calculators and reference tools for mechanical, electrical, civil, and industrial engineers who need quick, accurate answers without launching heavyweight simulation software. Whether you are calculating resistor values for a circuit board, converting between torque units for a motor specification, or determining the stress on a beam under load, these tools deliver reliable results based on standard engineering formulas and constants. Each calculator is designed to handle real-world inputs with appropriate units and precision, making them useful in the field, in the workshop, or at your desk. ToolNestr keeps the engineering tools free and accessible so you can double-check a critical value, convert between unit systems on the fly, or quickly run a standard calculation without interrupting your broader design workflow.",
    highlights: [
      "Calculate voltage, current, resistance, and power using Ohm's Law with support for parallel and series circuit configurations.",
      "Convert torque values between newton-meters, foot-pounds, inch-pounds, and kilogram-meters for cross-border engineering work.",
      "Determine beam deflection and stress under point and distributed loads using standard mechanical engineering formulas.",
      "Look up standard resistor color codes and calculate the resulting resistance value with tolerance and temperature coefficients.",
      "Estimate pipe flow rates and pressure drops using the Darcy-Weisbach equation for fluid system design and troubleshooting.",
      "Convert between engineering unit systems including SI, imperial, and US customary with high decimal precision maintained.",
    ],
  },
  construction: {
    intro: "The Construction category on ToolNestr delivers practical calculators and estimators that help contractors, builders, architects, and DIY homeowners plan projects with confidence. From calculating the number of concrete bags needed for a foundation to estimating paint coverage for a room, these tools turn rough guesses into precise material counts that save you time, money, and multiple trips to the hardware store. Each calculator is built around standard construction measurements and tolerances, accounting for waste factors and industry norms so your estimates are realistic. Whether you are laying flooring, framing a wall, pouring concrete, or ordering gravel for a driveway, ToolNestr gives you the numbers you need before you start spending. The tools are easy to use on any device, making them just as handy on a job site as they are at a desk.",
    highlights: [
      "Estimate concrete volume and bag count for slabs, columns, footings, and stairs with waste factors included automatically.",
      "Calculate paint and wallcovering needs based on room dimensions, number of coats, and surface texture for accurate ordering.",
      "Determine lumber and flooring material quantities for decks, patios, and interior rooms with standard board dimensions.",
      "Figure roof pitch, slope, and material coverage for shingles, tiles, or metal panels using simple rise-over-run inputs.",
      "Compute gravel, sand, and topsoil volumes in cubic yards or tons for landscaping, driveways, and foundation backfill.",
      "Estimate drywall, stud, and fastener counts for interior wall and ceiling framing based on room layout and spacing.",
    ],
  },
  cooking: {
    intro: "ToolNestr's Cooking and Kitchen category is a practical companion for home cooks, meal preppers, and professional chefs who need quick conversions and adjustments on the fly. Scale a recipe from four servings to forty, convert between volume and weight measurements for different ingredients, or figure out exactly how long to roast that turkey based on its weight. These tools account for common cooking realities like ingredient density differences and temperature conversions between Fahrenheit, Celsius, and gas marks. Instead of interrupting your cooking flow to do mental math or search through conversion charts, you get precise answers instantly. ToolNestr makes these utilities available in a clean, readable format that works well on a phone propped against the backsplash or a tablet on the counter, so you can keep your hands on the ingredients and your focus on the meal.",
    highlights: [
      "Scale any recipe up or down by serving count or ingredient percentage with all quantities recalculated automatically.",
      "Convert between volume units like cups, milliliters, teaspoons, and fluid ounces with ingredient-specific density adjustments.",
      "Convert oven temperatures between Fahrenheit, Celsius, and gas mark settings to follow recipes from any country.",
      "Calculate meat roasting and grilling times based on weight, cut, and desired doneness using standard cooking guidelines.",
      "Convert between weight and volume measurements for common ingredients like flour, sugar, butter, and liquids.",
      "Adjust ingredient ratios for baking substitutions such as replacing eggs, butter, or milk with alternative options.",
    ],
  },
  automotive: {
    intro: "The Automotive category on ToolNestr equips drivers, mechanics, and car enthusiasts with calculators that take the guesswork out of vehicle ownership and maintenance. Whether you are comparing fuel economy between two cars, figuring out a loan payment before visiting the dealership, or calculating the correct tire size for an upgrade, these tools deliver clear, accurate answers. The calculators cover practical real-world scenarios like estimated travel time based on distance and speed, brake stopping distances under different conditions, and horsepower-to-weight ratios for performance comparisons. Each tool uses standard automotive formulas and presents results in both metric and imperial units. ToolNestr keeps these utilities free and straightforward so you can make smarter decisions about buying, maintaining, and driving your vehicle without needing a garage full of specialized equipment.",
    highlights: [
      "Calculate fuel economy in miles per gallon or liters per hundred kilometers and estimate trip fuel costs by distance.",
      "Compare lease versus buy scenarios with monthly payment estimates, interest projections, and total cost of ownership.",
      "Determine the correct tire size upgrades and diameter changes when switching between wheel and tire combinations.",
      "Estimate 0-to-60 times and quarter-mile performance using horsepower, weight, and drivetrain configuration inputs.",
      "Compute stopping distances based on speed, reaction time, and road surface conditions for safer driving awareness.",
      "Convert engine displacement between liters, cubic inches, and cubic centimeters for comparing vehicle specifications.",
    ],
  },
  images: {
    intro: "ToolNestr's Image Tools offer a full suite of editing, conversion, and optimization utilities that handle the most common image tasks without the bloat of professional design software. Resize batches of photos for a website gallery, convert between PNG, JPEG, WebP, and GIF formats, compress high-resolution images for faster page loads, or extract frames from animated GIFs, all within your browser. Privacy is built into the design, every operation processes your files locally so they never leave your device. Whether you are an e-commerce merchant preparing product photos, a blogger optimizing featured images, or just someone who needs to shrink a photo before emailing it, these tools give you professional-grade results in seconds. ToolNestr supports common image formats and maintains quality throughout each transformation with configurable output settings.",
    highlights: [
      "Resize images by exact dimensions or percentage with intelligent cropping and aspect ratio lock options for uniformity.",
      "Convert between PNG, JPEG, WebP, BMP, and GIF formats while preserving metadata and adjusting quality levels.",
      "Compress JPEG and PNG images to reduce file size by up to 80 percent without visibly sacrificing image quality.",
      "Crop images to custom dimensions or preset aspect ratios like 16:9, 4:3, and 1:1 for social media and print layouts.",
      "Extract individual frames from animated GIFs and save them as separate image files for editing or reuse.",
      "Apply basic filters like grayscale, sepia, brightness, and contrast adjustments without uploading to an external server.",
    ],
  },
  security: {
    intro: "The Security Tools collection on ToolNestr helps you protect your digital life with straightforward utilities that generate, analyze, and verify credentials and data integrity. Create strong, memorable passwords that resist brute-force attacks, generate cryptographic hash values for file verification, or check whether your password has appeared in known data breaches. Each tool operates entirely in the browser so your sensitive information never crosses the network. This category also includes random token generators for API keys, entropy estimators that show you exactly how secure your passwords are, and text encryption utilities for basic privacy needs. ToolNestr designed these tools to make security best practices accessible to everyone, whether you are a casual user creating stronger login credentials or a developer testing hashing algorithms for a new application.",
    highlights: [
      "Generate cryptographically strong passwords with configurable length, character sets, and exclusion rules for easy typing.",
      "Check if a password has been exposed in known data breaches without sending your actual password over the internet.",
      "Compute file and text hashes using MD5, SHA-1, SHA-256, and SHA-512 to verify data integrity and authenticity.",
      "Estimate password entropy in bits to understand how long a brute-force attack would take against your chosen credentials.",
      "Generate random API keys, tokens, and secrets with configurable formats for application authentication and session management.",
      "Encrypt and decrypt short text messages using standard cipher algorithms for basic privacy in transit or at rest.",
    ],
  },
  text: {
    intro: "ToolNestr's Text Tools category is an essential utility kit for writers, editors, students, and anyone who works with written content on a regular basis. From cleaning up messy formatting and counting words to transforming case and comparing document differences, these tools handle the mechanical side of text so you can focus on the message. The collection includes a rich text editor, a diff checker that highlights changes between two versions, a case converter that handles everything from UPPERCASE to Title Case, and a line sorter that organizes content alphabetically or by length. Every tool processes your text instantly with no server uploads, preserving your privacy while giving you immediate results. ToolNestr makes these utilities available on any device, which is especially useful when you are editing on the go or need to prepare content for publication quickly.",
    highlights: [
      "Compare two text documents side by side with color-coded additions, deletions, and modifications highlighted for review.",
      "Count words, characters, lines, and paragraphs with real-time statistics that update as you type or paste content.",
      "Convert text case between uppercase, lowercase, title case, sentence case, and alternating case with one click.",
      "Remove duplicate lines, extra whitespace, empty paragraphs, and special characters to clean up messy content.",
      "Sort lines alphabetically, reverse alphabetically, or by line length for organizing lists, references, and data sets.",
      "Format text for Markdown, HTML, plain text, or code blocks with automatic escaping and structural conversion.",
    ],
  },
  seo: {
    intro: "The SEO Tools category on ToolNestr gives website owners, content marketers, and digital agencies the data they need to improve their search engine visibility without expensive enterprise subscriptions. Analyze keyword density in your content, preview how your pages will appear in Google search results, generate XML sitemaps, and check heading structure for proper hierarchy, all from one convenient dashboard. These tools help you identify common optimization opportunities like missing meta descriptions, weak title tags, and keyword cannibalization before they hurt your rankings. Each tool produces actionable output that you can implement directly, whether you are refining a blog post, auditing an entire site, or planning a content strategy. ToolNestr keeps SEO accessible by providing clear explanations alongside every result so you understand what each metric means and how to improve it.",
    highlights: [
      "Analyze keyword density and frequency in any text to optimize content for target search terms without over-optimization.",
      "Preview how your page title and meta description will appear in Google search results to improve click-through rates.",
      "Generate XML sitemaps for your website by entering a list of URLs or crawling a starting page automatically.",
      "Check heading structure hierarchy to ensure proper H1 through H6 usage for accessibility and search engine ranking signals.",
      "Estimate the readability score of your content using the Flesch-Kincaid scale to match your target audience level.",
      "Identify missing or duplicate meta titles and descriptions across your pages to fix common on-page SEO issues.",
    ],
  },
  converters: {
    intro: "ToolNestr's Converters category is the most comprehensive unit conversion hub you will find in any browser, covering virtually every measurement system used around the world. Whether you are converting currencies at live exchange rates, translating Celsius to Fahrenheit for a weather forecast, switching between metric and imperial units for a DIY project, or converting file formats for work, this collection has you covered. Each converter is built for precision, with support for decimal places, scientific notation, and batch conversions where applicable. The interface is consistent across every tool so once you learn one, you know them all. ToolNestr updates currency rates regularly and maintains accurate conversion factors for all other units, making this a reliable reference for students, travelers, engineers, and professionals in any field who need trustworthy conversions without ads or registration barriers.",
    highlights: [
      "Convert between over 150 global currencies using real-time exchange rates updated regularly throughout the trading day.",
      "Translate temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin with precise formulas and a visual comparison scale.",
      "Convert length, area, volume, mass, and speed between metric and imperial systems with up to ten decimal places.",
      "Swap file formats including documents, images, audio, and video without uploading sensitive files to external servers.",
      "Convert time zones across any cities worldwide with daylight saving time adjustments calculated automatically.",
      "Translate digital storage units from bytes to yottabytes with binary and decimal prefix options for accurate comparisons.",
    ],
  },
  'time-date': {
    intro: "The Time and Date category on ToolNestr provides a complete set of calendrical calculators and scheduling tools that help you navigate time zones, plan events, and compute durations with precision. Calculate the exact number of days between two dates for project planning, determine what day of the week a historical event fell on, or find the date that falls a certain number of business days from today, accounting for weekends and holidays. These tools are invaluable for project managers tracking deadlines, travelers coordinating across time zones, historians researching dates, and anyone managing schedules across different calendars. Each calculator handles edge cases like leap years, month-end dates, and regional holiday variations so you can trust the results. ToolNestr keeps time-date conversions simple and fast, turning what is often a tedious manual calculation into a one-click operation.",
    highlights: [
      "Calculate the exact number of days, months, and years between any two dates including or excluding weekends and holidays.",
      "Add or subtract business days from a date to find deadlines and delivery dates while skipping weekends automatically.",
      "Determine the day of the week for any date in history or the future using the Gregorian calendar algorithm.",
      "Convert between time zones for any cities worldwide with automatic daylight saving time adjustments applied.",
      "Find the age of a person or the duration since any event in years, months, weeks, days, hours, and minutes.",
      "Generate calendar months and years showing week numbers, holidays, and moon phases for planning and reference.",
    ],
  },
  charts: {
    intro: "ToolNestr's Charts and Graphs category makes data visualization accessible to everyone, regardless of design experience or statistical background. Transform rows of raw numbers into bar charts, line graphs, pie charts, and scatter plots that communicate your insights clearly and professionally. Simply paste your data, choose a chart type, and customize colors, labels, and dimensions to match your presentation or report style. Each chart renders instantly using lightweight browser-based rendering, and you can export the result as a high-resolution PNG or SVG image for use in documents, slides, or web pages. Whether you are a student visualizing survey results, a business analyst presenting quarterly metrics, or a blogger illustrating a trend, ToolNestr gives you the visual firepower you need without the steep learning curve of dedicated analytics software.",
    highlights: [
      "Create bar charts, line graphs, pie charts, and scatter plots from tabular data with customizable colors and labels.",
      "Export your finished charts as high-resolution PNG or scalable SVG images for use in presentations and publications.",
      "Customize every visual element including fonts, grid lines, axis ranges, legends, and background colors to match your brand.",
      "Paste data directly from spreadsheets or CSV files and watch your chart update in real time as you make edits.",
      "Add data labels, trend lines, and annotations to highlight key points and make your charts more informative.",
      "Generate multiple chart types from the same data set to find the visualization that best tells your story.",
    ],
  },
  networking: {
    intro: "The Networking Tools category on ToolNestr provides essential utilities for network administrators, IT support professionals, and anyone responsible for maintaining or troubleshooting computer networks. Perform DNS lookups, calculate subnet ranges, convert between IP addressing formats, and test network connectivity, all from a clean browser interface without installing command-line tools. Each utility is designed to handle the real-world scenarios that networking professionals face daily, from verifying that a domain resolves correctly before a website migration to calculating the optimal subnet mask for a new office deployment. The tools provide detailed output including reverse lookups, WHOIS information, and binary representations of addresses for educational purposes. ToolNestr makes these networking utilities available wherever you are, whether you are at a server rack, working remotely, or teaching networking concepts to students.",
    highlights: [
      "Perform DNS lookups for A, AAAA, MX, CNAME, TXT, and NS records to diagnose domain resolution and email delivery issues.",
      "Calculate subnet ranges, usable host addresses, and broadcast addresses from any IP and CIDR or subnet mask combination.",
      "Convert between binary, decimal, and hexadecimal IP address representations for troubleshooting and educational purposes.",
      "Run ping and traceroute simulations to identify network latency, packet loss, and routing path inefficiencies.",
      "Look up WHOIS information for any domain or IP address to identify registrants, name servers, and registration dates.",
      "Perform forward and reverse DNS lookups to verify PTR records and ensure proper email server authentication.",
    ],
  },
};

const content = categoryContent[catId];
const catLabel = `${category.emoji} ${category.name}`;
const siteTitle = `${catLabel} Tools`;

const itemListJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ItemList',
  itemListElement: catTools.map((t, i) => ({
    '@type': 'ListItem',
    position: i + 1,
    url: `${site.url}/tools/${t.slug}/`,
    name: t.title,
  })),
  numberOfItems: catTools.length,
};
---

<BaseLayout title={siteTitle} description={description} jsonLd={itemListJsonLd}>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-10">
    <nav class="mb-4 text-sm text-slate-500" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-indigo-600">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-1">›</span>
      <span class="text-slate-700">{category.name} Tools</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
      {catLabel} Tools
    </h1>
    {content?.intro && <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-lg text-slate-600">{content.intro}</p>}

    <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {catTools.map((tool) => <ToolCard tool={tool} />)}
    </div>

    {content?.highlights && (
      <section class="mt-14 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 sm:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Why use our {category.name} tools?</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
          {content.highlights.map((h) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-600">
              <span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-indigo-500">&#10003;</span>
              <span>{h}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
          All tools are free, private (they run in your browser), and work on any device.
          <a href="/" class="ml-1 font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline">Browse all categories →</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    )}

    {catTools.length === 0 && (
      <p class="mt-10 text-center text-slate-500">No tools in this category yet — check back soon.</p>
    )}
  </div>

  <!-- Other categories -->
  <section class="border-t border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-800/20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-12">
      <h2 class="text-center text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">More categories</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {categories.filter((c) => c.id !== catId).map((c) => {
          const total = totalInCategory(c.id);
          return (
            <a
              href={`/tools/${c.id}/`}
              class="group flex items-center gap-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 shadow-sm transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-indigo-200 hover:text-indigo-600 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-800/60 dark:text-slate-300 dark:hover:border-indigo-500/30 dark:hover:text-indigo-400"
            >
              <span>{c.emoji}</span>
              <span class="min-w-0 truncate">{c.name}</span>
              <span class="ml-auto shrink-0 text-xs text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-500">{total} tool{total !== 1 ? 's' : ''}</span>
            </a>
          );
        })}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
